'''薄皮蚤属'''（学名：{{lang|la|''Leptodora''}}）为[[薄皮蚤科|薄皮蚤科]]动物唯一的一個[[属|属]]。過往本屬只有'''透明薄皮蚤'''（学名：{{lang|la|''Leptodora kindtii''}}）一個[[物种|物种]]，直至2009年本屬的第二個物種被發現。這兩個物種在對比其他[[雙甲下綱|雙甲下綱]]物種來說比較大，近乎[[透明|透明及透光]]，是一類[[捕食|捕食性]]物種。本屬物種最長可長至{{convert|21|mm|abbr=on}}，有兩枝可用，作游泳的[[觸角|觸角]]，以及一隻[[複眼|複眼]]。腿可用作捕捉碰巧路過的[[橈足亞綱|橈足亞綱]]物種。

透明薄皮蚤見於[[北半球|北半球]]溫帶的湖泊中，很可能是枝角目物種當中唯一曾被[[報紙|報章]]報導過的[[生物分类学|已描述生物]]；而''L. richardi''現時只見於[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]][[俄羅斯遠東地區|遠東地區]]的[[黑龙江|黑龙江]]流域，儘管日本認為在其國內分佈的物種亦是''L. richardi''。
For most of the year, ''Leptodora'' reproduces <!-- [[parthenogenesis|parthenogenetically]] -->[[单性生殖|单性生殖]], with males only appearing late in the season, to produce winter eggs which hatch the following spring. ''Leptodora'' is the only genus in its family, the '''Leptodoridae''', and suborder, '''Haplopoda'''.

== 形態描述 ==
薄皮蚤屬物種的成體是北美洲原生[[浮游生物|浮游]]枝角目物種當中體型最大的<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cfb.unh.edu/CFBkey/html/Organisms/CCladocera/FLeptodoridae/GLeptodora/Leptodora_kindti/leptodorakindti.html |title=''Leptodora kindti'' |work=An Image-Based Key to the Zooplankton of the Northeast (USA) |publisher=[[新罕布什爾大學|University of New Hampshire]] |access-date=2010-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100726012546/http://cfb.unh.edu/CFBkey/html/Organisms/CCladocera/FLeptodoridae/GLeptodora/Leptodora_kindti/leptodorakindti.html |archive-date=2010-07-26 |dead-url=yes |language=en}}</ref>；至於到底有多大，各種報告間不盡相同，但雌性成體普遍可長至{{convert|12|mm|abbr=on}}長<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.4319/lo.1990.35.5.1091 |title=Trophic interactions of ''Leptodora'' in Lake Mendota |author1=Cynthia C. Lunte |author2=Chris Luecke |journal={{tsl|en|Limnology and Oceanography||Limnology and Oceanography}} |volume=35 |issue=5 |year=1990 |pages=1091–1100 |jstor=2837489|bibcode=1990LimOc..35.1091L }}</ref>，部分報告聲稱可長至{{convert|21|mm|abbr=on}}長<ref name="Andrews"/>。這些動物的身體約有98%是透明的<ref name="CMich">{{cite web |url=http://www.cst.cmich.edu/users/mcnau1as/zooplankton%20web/Leptodora%5CLeptodora.htm |title=''Leptodora kindti'' |work=Zooplankton of the Great Lakes |publisher=[[中密歇根大学|Central Michigan University]] |access-date=2010-03-10 |language=en}}</ref>，以避免被[[鱼|魚類]]獵食<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1093/plankt/fbi033 |title=Contrasting life histories of the predatory cladocerans ''Leptodora kindtii'' and ''Bythotrephes longimanus'' |author=Donn K. Branstrator |journal={{tsl|en|Journal of Plankton Research||Journal of Plankton Research}} |volume=27 |issue=6 |pages=569–585 |year=2005 |doi-access=free }}</ref>。
Lilljeborg notes:<ref name="Lill"/> <blockquote>{{Lang|de|Das Weibchen ist in so hohem Grade durchsichtig, in wahrem Sinne »wasserhell», dass oft nur die Bewegungen ihr Dasein in dem Wasser verrathen. Bei auffallendem Sonnenlicht wird gewöhnlich der Schatten früher als das Thier selbst entdeckt.}}</blockquote>
<blockquote>The female is transparent to such a high degree, literally "as clear as water", that her presence is often only given away by her movements. In bright sunlight, the shadow is normally seen before the animal itself.</blockquote>
The male is similarly transparent.<ref name="Lill"/> The abdomen is elongated, but the {{tsl|en|carapace||carapace}} is small and only covers the {{tsl|en|Brood pouch (Peracarida)||brood pouch}}.<ref name="CMich"/>

[[胸節|胸節]]的六對[[附肢|附肢]]形成一個「餵哺籃」，用以捕捉獵物<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.4319/lo.1995.40.4.0834 |title=Seasonal changes in size of the feeding basket of ''Leptodora kindtii'' (Focke) in Lago Maggiore as related to variations in prey size selection |author1=Marina Manca |author2=Patrizia Comoli |journal={{tsl|en|Limnology and Oceanography||Limnology and Oceanography}} |volume=40 |issue=4 |year=1995 |pages=834–838 |jstor=2838319|bibcode=1995LimOc..40..834M |doi-access=free }}</ref>。
The second <!-- [[antenna_(biology)|antennae]] -->[[觸角|觸角]] are used for swimming, while the first antennae are <!-- [[Vestigiality|rudimentary]] -->[[痕跡器官|痕跡器官]] in females but elongated in males, where they are used in <!-- [[sexual_reproduction|sexual reproduction]] -->[[有性生殖|有性生殖]].<ref name="CMich"/> There is a single large <!-- [[compound_eye|compound eye]] -->[[複眼|複眼]] which takes up much of the animal's head.<ref name="CMich"/> It comprises around 500 {{tsl|en|facet||facet}}s, which are spherically arranged, and the whole eye is movable by up to 10° in any direction.<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1083/jcb.26.3.968 |journal={{tsl|en|Journal of Cell Biology||Journal of Cell Biology}} |year=1965 |volume=26 |issue=3 |pages=968–973 |pmid=19866691 |title=The compound eye of a crustacean, ''Leptodora kindtii'' |author1=J. J. Wolken |author2=G. J. Gallik |pmc=2106796}}</ref>

== 分佈 ==
透明薄皮蚤廣泛分佈於[[北半球|北半球]]溫帶的湖泊中，見於北美洲、[[亚洲|亚洲]]、[[欧洲|欧洲]]及[[非洲|非洲]]。在[[北美洲|北美洲]]，其分佈範圍南至[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]及[[俄克拉荷馬州|俄克拉荷馬州]]<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.2307/3671192 |title=Discovery of ''Leptodora kindtii'' (Focke) (Crustacea: Clad-Ocera) in Oklahoma and Texas |author1=Jack R. Holt |author2=David S. White |author3=Alan P. Covich |journal=[[The_Southwestern_Naturalist|The Southwestern Naturalist]] |volume=23 |issue=4 |year=1978 |pages=686–688 |jstor=3671192 |language=en}}</ref>；在[[中国大陆|中国大陆]]分佈於[[浙江|浙江]]、[[江苏|江苏]]、[[安徽|安徽]]、[[江西|江西]]、[[湖北|湖北]]、[[吉林|吉林]]、[[黑龙江|黑龙江]]、[[云南|云南]]、[[内蒙古|内蒙古]]等地<ref name='id12282'/>，主要栖息于大中型湖泊的敞水区、也出现在沿岸以及小型湖泊与积水较深的池塘中<ref name='id12282'/>。在[[欧洲|欧洲]]、[[北非|北非]]部分地區、[[阿拉伯半岛|阿拉伯半岛]]北部及[[亚洲|亚洲]][[喜马拉雅山脉|喜马拉雅山脉]]以北地區亦有分佈<ref name="CMich"/>。

== 生態及行為 ==
[[File:Daphnia_pulex.png|thumb]]物種（''[[Daphnia|Daphnia]]''）是[[透明薄皮蚤|透明薄皮蚤]]（''[[Leptodora_kindtii|Leptodora kindtii]]''）的其中一種重要獵物。]]
[[File:ForseBaar.JPG|thumb]]（''[[Perca_fluviatilis|Perca fluviatilis]]''）又是薄皮蚤屬動物的主要捕食者。]]
透明薄皮蚤是一種貪婪的捕食者，能夠控制其偏愛獵物的數量<ref name="Neusiedl">{{cite journal |author=Alois Herzig |s2cid=7755718 |year=1995 |title=''Leptodora kindti'': efficient predator and preferred prey item in Neusiedler See, Austria |journal={{tsl|en|Hydrobiologia||Hydrobiologia}} |volume=307 |issue=1–3 |pages=273–282 |editor1=P. Larsson |editor2=L. J. Weider |doi=10.1007/BF00032021}}</ref>，一般都是[[溞属|溞属]]（''Daphnia''）、''{{tsl|en|Bosmina||Bosmina}}'', ''{{tsl|en|Ceriodaphnia||Ceriodaphnia}}'', ''{{tsl|en|Diaphanosoma||Diaphanosoma}}'', ''{{tsl|en|Diaptomus||Diaptomus}}'', ''{{tsl|en|Polyphemus (genus)||Polyphemus}}''及[[剑水蚤属|剑水蚤属]]（''Cyclops''）等各屬物種的幼體<ref name="CMich"/>。 It seems to encounter its prey by chance, with contact initiating a <!-- [[reflex|reflex]] -->[[反射_(生理学)|反射 (生理学)]], in which the <!-- [[abdomen|abdomen]] -->[[腹|腹]] is brought forward to close the feeding basket. In many cases, the prey escapes this haphazard response. Juvenile ''Daphnia'' are slower than adults to respond to the predator's attack, and are therefore more likely to be caught.<ref name="Browman">{{cite journal |doi=10.1093/plankt/11.5.1075 |author1=Howard I. Browman |author2=Silke Kruse |author3=W. John O'Brien |year=1989 |title=Foraging behavior of the predaceous cladoceran, ''Leptodora kindti'', and escape responses of their prey |journal={{tsl|en|Journal of Plankton Research||Journal of Plankton Research}} |volume=11 |issue=5 |pages=1075–1088 }}</ref>

The most important predators of ''Leptodora'' are fishes, including <!-- [[Coregonus|whitefish]] -->[[白鮭屬|白鮭屬]], <!-- 頁面不存在 -->[[European_perch|perch]], {{tsl|en|ziege||ziege}} and <!-- [[Common_Bleak|bleak]] -->[[歐白魚|歐白魚]].<ref name="Neusiedl"/>

In <!-- [[Lake_Biwa|Lake Biwa]] -->[[琵琶湖|琵琶湖]], <!-- [[Japan|Japan]] -->[[日本|日本]], ''L. kindtii'' is <!-- [[parasitism|parasitised]] -->[[寄生|寄生]] by the <!-- [[nematode|nematode]] -->[[线虫动物门|线虫动物门]] ''<!-- 頁面不存在 -->[[Raphidascaris_biwakoensis|Raphidascaris biwakoensis]]'', a parasite of <!-- [[fish|fish]] -->[[鱼|鱼]].<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.3354/dao032157 |author1=F. Moravec |author2=K. Nasagawa |author3=Y. Tanaka |author4=T. Narita |year=1998 |journal=<!-- 頁面不存在 -->[[Diseases_of_Aquatic_Organisms|Diseases of Aquatic Organisms]] |volume=32 |pages=157–160 |title=Role of ''Leptodora kindti'' (Cladocera: Leptodoridae) in the life cycle of ''Raphidascaris biwakoensis'' (Nematoda: Anisakidae), a fish parasite in Lake Biwa, Japan |issue=2 |pmid=9676256 |url=https://www.int-res.com/articles/dao/32/d032p157.pdf |doi-access=free }}</ref>

==Life cycle==
Female ''Leptodora'' produce a brood of eggs through <!-- [[parthenogenesis|parthenogenesis]] -->[[单性生殖|单性生殖]] every 12 hours.<ref name="Vijv"/> These eggs hatch into a <!-- [[larva|larva]] -->[[幼体|幼体]]l stage about {{convert|2|mm}} long. There are six further {{tsl|en|instar||instar}}s before the adult form is reached with a length of {{convert|6|mm}}.<ref name="Vijv">{{cite journal |title=Effect of temperature on development and growth of the raptorial cladoceran ''Leptodora kindtii'' under laboratory conditions |author1=Jacobus Vijverberg |author2=Hans Peter Koelewijn |journal=<!-- [[Freshwater_Biology|Freshwater Biology]] -->[[淡水生物學|淡水生物學]] |volume=49 |pages=1415–1422 |year=2004 |doi=10.1111/j.1365-2427.2004.01276.x |issue=11}}</ref> The time taken to reach adulthood is temperature dependent, but takes between 3 and 6 days.<ref name="Vijv"/> For most of the year, reproduction is parthenogenetic, with eggs being produced by females without males being present in the population.<ref name="CMich"/> In the autumn, parthenogenetically produced males begin to appear;<ref name="Andrews">{{cite journal |doi=10.2307/3223355 |title=Growth studies on parthenogenetically produced male and female ''Leptodora kindtii'' (Focke) |author=Ted F. Andrews |journal={{tsl|en|Transactions of the American Microscopical Society||Transactions of the American Microscopical Society}} |volume=72 |issue=1 |year=1953 |pages=9–17 |jstor=3223355}}</ref> males and females then <!-- [[sexual_reproduction|reproduce sexually]] -->[[有性生殖|有性生殖]]. The resulting eggs sink to the bottom where they <!-- [[overwintering|overwinter]] -->[[越冬|越冬]],<ref name="Lill"/> hatching the following year as {{tsl|en|nauplius (larva)||nauplius}}-like larvae.<ref name="CMich"/>

==Related taxa==
''Leptodora'' is so distinct from other cladocerans that some authors have suggested grouping all other cladocerans into a <!-- [[clade|clade]] -->[[演化支|演化支]] called "Eucladocera", with ''Leptodora'' as its <!-- [[sister_group|sister group]] -->[[姐妹群|姐妹群]]. It is now believed, however, that ''Leptodora'' is sister to {{tsl|en|Onychopoda||Onychopoda}}, being the only genus in the family '''Leptodoridae''' and the subclass '''Haplopoda'''.<ref name="M&D">{{cite book |url=http://atiniui.nhm.org/pdfs/3839/3839.pdf |title=An Updated Classification of the Recent Crustacea |author1=Joel W. Martin |author2=George E. Davis |year=2001 |pages=132 |publisher=<!-- [[Natural_History_Museum_of_Los_Angeles_County|Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County]] -->[[洛杉磯縣自然歷史博物館|洛杉磯縣自然歷史博物館]]}}</ref> Features which separate it from other families include its large size, the lack of branchial appendages (<!-- [[gill|gill]] -->[[鳃|鳃]]s) on its legs, the reduction of the carapace, and the fact that the winter eggs hatch as nauplii.<ref name="CMich"/>

==Taxonomic history==
[[File:Water_trench,_Bremen_09.JPG|thumb]]
''Leptodora kindtii'' is "probably the only cladoceran ever described in a newspaper".<ref name="Dumont">{{cite journal |title=''Leptodora kindtii'' (Focke, 1844) from Bremen, Germany: discovered, forgotten, and rediscovered |author1=Henri J. Dumont |author2=Werner Hollwedel |journal={{tsl|en|Crustaceana||Crustaceana}} |volume=82 |issue=11 |year=2009 |pages=1457–1461 |doi=10.1163/001121609X12511103974457}}</ref> The German microscopist {{tsl|en|Gustav Woldemar Focke||Gustav Woldemar Focke}} organised a <!-- [[scientific_meeting|scientific meeting]] -->[[學術研討會|學術研討會]] in <!-- [[Bremen|Bremen]] -->[[不来梅|不来梅]] in 1844 together with the pharmacist Georg Christian Kindt. He studied the fauna of the ditches surrounding the city (the ''{{lang|de|Bremer Stadtgraben}}'') and displayed live specimens at the meeting. During the meeting, he also published a description of the species in the ''{{Lang|de|<!-- 頁面不存在 -->[[Weser-Zeitung|Weser-Zeitung]]}}'' on Sunday September 22, 1844, placing the species in the genus ''{{tsl|en|Polyphemus (genus)||Polyphemus}}''.<ref name="Dumont"/> However, this description was ignored by the scientific community, and {{tsl|en|Wilhelm Lilljeborg||Wilhelm Lilljeborg}} described the species in 1861 with the name ''Leptodora hyalina''. The <!-- [[synonym_(taxonomy)|synonymy]] -->[[異名|異名]] was not noticed until Simon Albrecht Poppe informed Lilljeborg of it in 1889,<ref name="Dumont"/> and Lilljeborg corrected the error in his 1900 <!-- [[monograph|monograph]] -->[[專著|專著]].<ref name="Lill">{{cite book |author=Wilhelm Lilljeborg |year=1900 |title=Cladocera Sueciae; oder Beiträge zur kenntniss der in Schweden lebenden Krebsthiere von der Ordnung der Branchiopoden und der Unterordnung der Cladoceren |publisher=Druck der Akademischen buchdruckerei E. Berling |location=<!-- [[Uppsala|Uppsala]] -->[[乌普萨拉|乌普萨拉]] |url=https://archive.org/details/cladocerasueciae00lill |pages=[https://archive.org/details/cladocerasueciae00lill/page/650 650]–658, Tab. 87|author-link=Wilhelm Lilljeborg }}</ref>

2009年，Korovchinsky首度為本屬的第二個物種''Leptodora richardii''作出描述：這個物種採樣自[[黑龙江|黑龙江]]盆地的湖泊，包括[[博隆湖|博隆湖]]<ref name="Korovchinsky 2009">{{cite journal |first=Nikolai M. |last=Korovchinsky |year=2009 |title=The genus ''Leptodora'' Lilljeborg (Crustacea: Branchiopoda: Cladocera) is not monotypic: description of a new species from the Amur River basin (Far East of Russia) |journal=''[[Zootaxa|Zootaxa]]'' |volume=2120 |pages=39–52 |url=http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2009/f/z02120p052f.pdf |doi=10.11646/zootaxa.2120.1.5 |language=en}}</ref>。

